==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pretext
<hw>Pre"text</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧texte</ets>, L. <ets>praetextum</ets>, fr.
<ets>praetextus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>praetexere</ets> to weave before,
allege as an excuse; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>texere</ets> to
weave. See <er>Text</er>.]</ety> <def>Ostensible reason or motive
assigned or assumed as a color or cover for the real reason or motive;
pretense; disguise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They suck the blood of those they depend on, under a
<qex>pretext</qex> of service and kindness.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With how much or how little <qex>pretext</qex> of reason.</q>
<rj><qau>Dr. H. More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Pretense; excuse; semblance; disguise;
appearance. See <er>Pretense</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pretexture</ent>⟦br⟧
